Read input data

Source: R/read_input_dat.R
read_input_dat.Rd

Read input data

Usage

read_input_dat(input_dat, input_CRS, to_CRS_M, XY = NULL)

Arguments

input_dat

CSV file containing XY or any shape file formats.

input_CRS

Integer input. CRS of input data as EPSG code

to_CRS_M

Integer input. Corresponding CRS in unit M to input CRS as EPSG code

XY

a vector identifying colnames of X and Y e.g. c("Easting", "Northing")

Value

A sf object with CRS

Examples

cornersData
#>                       X                      Y id
#> 1 148.68700210018400298 -34.470635525918503106  1
#> 2 148.68725442979499007 -34.470617022818302644  4
#> 3 148.68692120078898711 -34.469923377899100103  2
#> 4 148.68717201792100013 -34.469903781106502549  3

dat <- read_input_dat(cornersData, 4326, 28355)
